# Development and test dependencies ONLY — the runtime set lives in requirements.in.
# The previous single requirements.txt shipped black/flake8/mypy/pytest to production.
#
# Compile (dev is constrained by the runtime lockfile so the two can never disagree on a
# shared transitive dependency — installing dev must not silently change a runtime pin):
#
#   pip-compile --upgrade requirements.in     -o requirements.txt
#   pip-compile --upgrade requirements-dev.in -o requirements-dev.txt -c requirements.txt
#
# Install for development:
#
#   pip install -r requirements.txt -r requirements-dev.txt
#
# Install for production:
#
#   pip install -r requirements.txt

# The suite is integration-style: it drives a live server over HTTP and talks to Mongo
# directly for role fixtures. `pymongo` arrives via motor in the runtime set.
